New checker - openvpn
CVE Data - https://www.cvedetails.com/product-list/vendor_id-3278/Openvpn.html
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50541438/81453462-3734e200-91a7-11ea-94d5-886d78e48075.png)
Strings found used in regex
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 423301283, 'comment_body': "I don't think we need both test-open.vpn.2.4.0.out and test-openvpn.2.4.0.out  (and ditto for the 2.3.13 version)  What were you trying to do here?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 11, 20, 31, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'terriko', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 423318055, 'comment_body': 'In these cases the second if condition
    if version != "UNKNOWN" and "is_or_contains" not in version_info:
will be true, thus increasing the coverage of the checker.
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 11, 21, 2, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SaurabhK122', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424014852, 'comment_body': 'Yeah, but you're doing this twice, which isn't increasing coverage because it's testing exactly the same thing.  Let's keep `test-openvpn.2.4.0.c` (to test the "is" case) and `test-open.vpn.2.3.13.c` (to test the "contains" case) and ditch the other two.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 20, 31, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'terriko', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424028300, 'comment_body': 'Yes, you are right. I have made the required changes.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 12, 20, 56, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SaurabhK122', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424595550, 'comment_body': 'It should be OpenvpnChecker', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 13, 17, 5, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Niraj-Kamdar', 'type': 'User'}]
